1
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,440
Thank you, Officer Ran.

2
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,960
Oh, what's with all these gifts?

3
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,480
- You shouldn't have.
- Chinese New Year is almost here.

4
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,560
Anyway, Officer Ran,

5
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,200
about the person named Yao Xincheng

6
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,280
you asked about,

7
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,480
I really don't remember anything.

8
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:00,800
I never heard Uncle or Mengmeng
mention that name either.

9
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,560
Uncle and Mengmeng
have been gone for five years now.

10
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,960
The police also announced that.

11
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,280
Wasn't the killer already dead?

12
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:10,520
How is this still not over?

13
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,560
If the truth hasn't come out,
how can it be over?

14
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,320
Even if I'm gone,

15
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:26,120
other police officers
will keep investigating.

16
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,280
Right.

17
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,400
Please think carefully again.

18
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:34,920
<i>What did Officer Ran say to you?</i>

19
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,560
<i>What did he ask about?</i>

20
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,600
I remember

21
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:41,600
Officer Ran made a phone call here.

22
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,520
He called someone

23
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:46,440
with a two-character name.
Something Qiang.

24
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:47,920
Qiang?

25
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,400
Ma Qiang…

26
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:53,280
- Was it Ma Qiang?
- <i>Yes.</i>

27
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,720
<i>That's it. Ma Qiang.</i>

28
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,880
Ma Qiang… One moment.

29
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,440
Right away.

30
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,280
Alright. You can send it now.

31
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:09,800
<i>Officer Ran, other than 1997 and 2002,</i>

32
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:12,200
- <i>do you want the rest too?</i>
- Yes.

33
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,360
I have those two years.

34
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,040
Please send me the resident lists

35
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,840
- for all the other years.
- <i>Alright. Right away.</i>

36
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,320
RESIDENT LIST

37
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,840
POLICE INTELLIGENCE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM

38
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:52,920
"YAO XINCHENG" SEARCH RESULTS

39
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,120
DAD

40
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,320
Dad,

41
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,840
I've searched both the internal network
and the public internet.

42
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:04,960
There are all kinds of Yao Xinchengs.

43
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:05,720
"YAO XINCHENG" SEARCH RESULTS

44
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,840
Either they're not in Weiyang

45
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:09,400
or they don't match Mr. Lu's description.

46
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,600
Any leads on your side?

47
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,720
Xu Meng's family doesn't know this person.

48
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,120
I also asked Su Yuzhi and Lili.

49
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,920
<i>They don't know this name either.</i>

50
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:23,920
Qian Dajun cut the power again!

51
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:27,080
Tomorrow, I'll cut his life short!

52
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,240
<i>Dad.</i>

53
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:31,120
Is everything alright in Yuanlongli?

54
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,200
<i>Is Qian Dajun starting something again?</i>

55
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,200
He's long gone now.

56
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,280
After smashing the windows last night,

57
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,280
everyone's waiting to deal with him.

58
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,120
Kiddo, go to work tomorrow.

59
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,400
If I find any clues here,
I'll let you know.

60
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,720
- Hello?
- Hello?

61
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,280
Dad?

62
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,720
NO SERVICE

63
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,240
Jeez.

64
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,080
Ma Qiang.

65
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:01,840
Mr. He.

66
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,960
I called you. Why didn't you answer?

67
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:08,840
I'm sorry, Mr. He.
I was with Mr. Qian all night.

68
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,040
I didn't dare answer. What do you need?

69
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,120
The night before New Year's Eve in 2003,

70
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,600
did Officer Ran call you?

71
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,880
That was so long ago.
How could I remember?

72
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,400
The day before Ran passed away.

73
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:31,200
Yes, I remember now. Officer Ran
called me then and asked

74
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:32,640
for Yuanlongli's resident lists
from the past years.

75
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,120
Later, he came
to the property office himself

76
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,400
and even brought New Year gifts.

77
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,840
YUANLONGLI PROPERTY MANAGEMENT

78
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:40,200
Thank you, Officer Ran. You're too kind.

79
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,360
You still remember us.

80
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,360
Have a seat.

81
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,560
Please sit.

82
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,640
It's almost Chinese New Year.
You all work hard year-round.

83
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:53,640
Our job can't compare to yours at all.

84
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,680
By the way,

85
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:58,520
do you remember
if there was someone in Yuanlongli

86
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,920
named Yao Xincheng?

87
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,760
Yao Xincheng?

88
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,600
I really don't know.

89
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,920
What about relatives of the residents?

90
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:08,280
I know even less about that.

91
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,280
Where's Mr. Qian?

92
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,160
I called him several times,
but he didn't answer.

93
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,200
Mr. Qian went out
this afternoon for business drinks.

94
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:22,560
At this hour,
he's probably hammered already.

95
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,120
Officer Ran,

96
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,440
I'm about to head back
to my village for Chinese New Year.

97
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,080
Wang Xinglong is on duty tomorrow.

98
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,040
How about this?

99
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,520
I'll leave a note for Mr. Qian.

100
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,600
When he sees it, he'll call you back.

101
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,320
Alright.

102
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,800
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

103
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,280
Officer Ran.

104
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:45,800
You mentioned this Yao Xincheng.

105
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,440
Does he have anything to do
with Yuanlongli?

106
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,800
If he has nothing to do
with Yuanlongli either,

107
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:02,560
then I don't know where I can go next.

108
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:08,320
And then?

109
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,520
And then…

110
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:12,000
That was all.

111
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:16,000
When Officer Ran left,
he looked pretty disappointed.

112
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,680
I never thought

113
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:28,320
that would be the last time I saw him.

114
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,480
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

115
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,400
<i>Say, sir,</i>

116
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,680
<i>do you remember the blue leather heels</i>
<i>from the June 30th case?</i>

117
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:21,200
<i>The blue leather heels</i>
<i>were tall and eye-catching.</i>

118
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,240
<i>They were definitely real.</i>

119
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,160
BLUE LEATHER HEELS
LILI

120
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,080
DU MINGLIANG'S MOTHER

121
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:26,720
<i>You should ask those who sell fake shoes.</i>

122
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,400
<i>They would definitely know.</i>

123
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:31,040
<i>Judging by the finish and workmanship,</i>

124
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,720
<i>that should be the work</i>
<i>of Mr. Lu from Pingzhao County.</i>

125
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:36,600
<i>It was a perfectly real pair of shoes,</i>
<i>yet he insisted I make them look fake.</i>

126
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,640
<i>He was a man in his thirties.</i>

127
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,679
SHOEMAKER MR. LU
MAN WITH THREE CIGARETTE BURN MARKS

128
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:42,440
<i>He had three burn marks on his arm.</i>

129
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,880
<i>There's a loose thread here.</i>

130
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,960
<i>How did I never notice it before?</i>

131
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:47,720
BOWLS DRESS

132
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,320
<i>According to the dry-cleaning records,</i>

133
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:53,040
<i>the buyer of this dress</i>
<i>was named Yao Xincheng.</i>

134
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:56,240
<i>If he has nothing to do with Yuanlongli,</i>

135
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:59,200
<i>then I don't know where I can go next.</i>

136
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,560
Ran.

137
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:25,240
How did you continue the investigation?

138
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Sir,

139
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,760
if you were me,

140
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,480
how would you continue the investigation?

141
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:42,720
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH

142
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:46,880
LOYAL AND TRUE

143
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,560
Hello, Dad?

144
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,120
What did you find?

145
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:56,480
- I'm going home.
- What? Not investigating anymore?

146
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,960
<i>I was thinking</i>
<i>I would come to your place after work.</i>

147
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,920
The trail went cold.

148
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,840
I don't want to stay stuck
in Yuanlongli anymore.

149
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:04,960
I'll head home

150
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,080
and think about the next move.

151
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:08,880
Alright then.

152
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,960
I'll help you move after work.

153
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,960
No need. You take care of your work.

154
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,720
I can handle these myself.

155
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:19,160
Dad,

156
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,800
are you alright?

157
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,600
Why wouldn't I be?

158
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,360
Just focus on your job.

159
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:31,880
<i>If I find any new clues,</i>
<i>I'll tell you right away.</i>

160
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:37,520
Don't worry. In my life,
there's no such word as giving up.

161
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,040
I'm hanging up.

162
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,120
Coming.

163
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,160
Who is it?

164
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,800
Officer He, morning.

165
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:44,640
Manager Ma sent me over
to bring you hot water.

166
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:47,120
There's no need.

167
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,120
I'm moving out soon anyway.

168
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,680
Are you moving out?

169
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,240
That's great.

170
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,840
I'll give you a hand.

171
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:59,120
No need. You go get busy.

172
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,200
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

173
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:10,040
Poor Officer Ran.

174
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:14,000
Speaking of that,

175
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,520
before he passed, I saw him one last time.

176
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,280
Then…

177
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,520
What did you say?

178
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,760
You saw him? When?

179
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,800
On New Year's Eve morning.

180
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:34,640
In this building.

181
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,880
Who the heck is that?

182
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,560
I'm sorry, Wang Xinglong.

183
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,000
Officer Ran?

184
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,240
It's alright.

185
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,040
You really startled me.

186
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,840
<i>When he came out of the elevator,</i>
<i>he scared me.</i>

187
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,400
His eyes were bloodshot.

188
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,840
He clearly didn't sleep all night.

189
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,520
<i>Then he rushed off in a hurry.</i>

190
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:03,600
Must've been heading off
to something urgent.

191
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:11,200
Are you sure
it was New Year's Eve morning?

192
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:15,000
I'm sure. Eight in the morning.

193
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,720
It was a property management rule.

194
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:19,160
Eight a.m. Patrol the building at 8 a.m.

195
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:21,800
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE

196
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,240
SAVED TIME: 2003-01-31
13:09:37, RECIPIENT: SIR

197
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,720
RAN: SIR, THE JUNE 30TH CASE IS WRONG
THE WHOLE THING IS WRONG

198
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,120
Thank you.

199
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,040
You did me a big favor.

200
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,520
Wait, Mr. He… Weren't you moving out?

201
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,440
Why are you moving things back in?

202
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:43,960
I'm not moving anymore.
Absolutely not moving.

203
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:47,920
By the way,
go find Qian Dajun now and tell him

204
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,800
I'm staying in Yuanlongli,
and I'll fight him to the end.

205
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,080
That's a snap decision.

206
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:05,480
Ran met with Ma Qiang

207
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,600
the night before New Year's Eve.

208
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,280
Then on New Year's Eve morning,

209
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:13,200
he ran out of the building again.

210
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:16,760
His eyes were red with exhaustion.

211
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:21,040
That afternoon, he drafted a message to me

212
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:24,080
saying the June 30th case was all wrong.

213
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:28,320
He must have found something.

214
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:32,280
He must have found something
in this building.

215
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:33,200
<i>CRIMINAL CASE STUDIES</i>

216
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,280
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

217
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,720
Ran,

218
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,240
what did you find?

219
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:24,480
SIR

220
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,880
<i>In four hours,</i>
<i>we'll welcome the Chinese New Year.</i>

221
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,800
<i>On the last night</i>
<i>before the fresh new year,</i>

222
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:53,920
<i>are you, listening to the radio,</i>
<i>on your way to reunite with your family?</i>

223
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,760
BLESSING

224
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:23,880
Why won't he answer?

225
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,320
Dad, don't worry.

226
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,760
Uncle Ran has probably gone
to pick up Ms. Qiao.

227
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,200
See? Here they are.

228
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,200
Coming.

229
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,960
- Qiao.
- Officer He.

230
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:42,080
Ms. Qiao.

231
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:43,800
- Xiaohe.
- Come in.

232
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:44,560
Sure.

233
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:46,880
Ran didn't come with you?

234
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,480
I thought something had come up
at work and kept him busy.

235
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:54,200
He was supposed to pick me up from work.

236
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:56,800
I waited, and he never showed.

237
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:57,840
He didn't answer my calls either.

238
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,400
I was worried
you would all be waiting too long,

239
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,520
so I took a taxi here.

240
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:04,320
That brat.

241
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,320
What is he busy with on New Year's Eve?

242
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,240
Maybe he left his phone back at work.

243
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:12,360
It's raining hard outside today.
The roads are bad.

244
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:13,680
Let's wait for him.

245
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,200
Alright. Let's go inside.

246
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:19,800
Officer He, I'm not good at picking gifts,

247
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:21,440
so I brought some supplements.

248
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:23,080
Just having you here is enough.

249
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,760
You don't have to bring
anything next time.

250
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,840
Xiaohe, help Ms. Qiao change clothes

251
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:27,880
- and get her a pair of slippers.
- Okay.

252
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:29,360
I'll finish wrapping dumplings.

253
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,120
- Ms. Qiao, here.
- Thank you.

254
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,320
Come. New Year's gift.

255
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:42,160
We have the same scarf.
Thank you, Ms. Qiao.

256
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,280
You're welcome.

257
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,760
Have a seat.

258
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:47,680
Sure.

259
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,480
This scarf matches my hairstyle perfectly.

260
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,120
By the way,
did Uncle Ran get you a gift too?

261
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,280
Oh…

262
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,760
Looks like the answer is obvious.

263
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:07,840
Officer He, I'll help.

264
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,720
Alright. Good to have extra hands.

265
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:16,800
Qiao,

266
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,480
my apprentice is good in every way.

267
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:22,320
Stable job.

268
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:24,440
Good character.

269
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:26,000
Only one flaw.

270
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:29,200
Other than solving cases,
he never takes the initiative in anything.

271
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:35,080
You see, as his mentor,
when it comes to marriage,

272
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:37,120
I can count as half a parent.

273
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:39,640
Look,

274
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:41,040
Xiaohe likes you so much.

275
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,720
Our big family here
just happens to be missing one person.

276
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:47,080
We genuinely hope
you'll become that person.

277
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:49,280
That's right, Ms. Qiao.

278
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:52,320
From the first time I met you,
I felt like you would become family.

279
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:54,240
Once Uncle Ran gets here,

280
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,640
I'm calling you Mrs. Ran.

281
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,560
Qiao,

282
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,600
no matter how things develop
between you and Ran later,

283
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,640
fast or slow, that's between you two.

284
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:05,640
I won't interfere.

285
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,280
But one thing I'll say first.

286
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:09,680
This home will be your home from now on.

287
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:13,160
We gather like this
every holiday and festival.

288
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:44,800
In a little while,
the New Year bell will ring.

289
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,680
I should make a wish.

290
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,960
I wish our whole family

291
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:52,960
happiness and many blessings.

292
00:21:57,080 --> 00:21:58,120
Thank you,

293
00:21:58,640 --> 00:21:59,480
Officer He.

294
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:01,520
Thank you, Xiaohe.

295
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,840
And even more, I should thank Ran.

296
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:07,600
Thank you all

297
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:10,600
for making me feel
what having a family is like.

298
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,760
That's my wish too.

299
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,680
My New Year's wish.

300
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:19,720
Why thank us?

301
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,440
From now on, we're family.

302
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:23,880
No need for thanks between family.

303
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,520
Exactly.

304
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,640
No worries there, Mrs. Ran.

305
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:32,040
<i>I want love to live in my home every day</i>

306
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,480
<i>Day and night</i>

307
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,440
<i>Through all four seasons</i>

308
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,040
<i>With our hearts</i>

309
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:38,880
<i>Loving our home</i>

310
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:42,280
<i>I want love to live in your home every day</i>

311
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,600
<i>I want love to live in my home every day</i>

312
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,240
<i>Filled with joy</i>

313
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,520
<i>Safe and blessed</i>

314
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,960
<i>Love stays in our home</i>

315
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:51,720
RAN

316
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:55,360
<i>Forever</i>

317
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:34,640
SIR

318
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,240
It's mainly because of the oil drums.

319
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:08,880
Recheck the scene.

320
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,320
Director Zou, this belongs to Captain Ran.

321
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:18,080
It's burned in the fire.

322
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,360
There are no cameras on this road.

323
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,680
Based on our initial investigation,

324
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:27,720
the accident was likely caused
by poorly stored materials

325
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,560
at this construction site.

326
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,560
Strong wind knocked over two fuel drums.

327
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,280
It was raining hard and dark outside.

328
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:37,080
Oil spilled onto the road,
making it slippery.

329
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:41,400
When the vehicle passed through,
it would've been hard to keep control.

330
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,240
That's why Captain Ran…

331
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:48,160
Coordinate with the criminal department.

332
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,360
You must get to the bottom of this.

333
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,920
He was a good coworker

334
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,520
and a good comrade.

335
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:00,160
It's heartbreaking.

336
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:11,400
Uncle Ran!

337
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,320
Uncle Ran!

338
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,720
- Uncle Ran!
- Xiaohe.

339
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:16,880
Don't go over there.

340
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:20,560
Don't. Xiaohe, don't go over there.

341
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:01,720
Ran.

342
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,160
It's Chinese New Year.

343
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,680
It's Chinese New Year.

344
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:33,880
<i>Wishing everyone a Happy Chinese New Year!</i>

345
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:35,680
- <i>Wish you a happy Year of the Goat!</i>
- <i>Happy New Year!</i>

346
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:37,640
<i>Happy Chinese New Year!</i>

347
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:40,440
<i>Dear friends, at this exciting moment,</i>

348
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:42,440
<i>we send to people</i>
<i>of all ethnic groups across the nation,</i>

349
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,120
<i>to our compatriots</i>

350
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,160
<i>in Hong Kong, China,</i>
<i>Macau Special Administrative Region,</i>

351
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:48,280
<i>Taiwan, China, and to Chinese people</i>
<i>all around the world</i>

352
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:49,200
<i>our New Year greetings.</i>

353
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:52,800
<i>Crossing the threshold of time,</i>
<i>we step into the embrace of spring.</i>

354
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:54,960
<i>Happy Spring Festival!</i>

355
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:18,160
RAN FANGXU, MALE, CREMATION IN PROGRESS

356
00:30:18,240 --> 00:30:21,760
IN PROGRESS

357
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:27,600
IN MOURNING

358
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,880
Xiaohe, where are you going?

359
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,760
- I win.
- That's your…

360
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,160
Someone's here.

361
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:16,160
LANYA HAIR SALON

362
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:18,320
FULL SALON SERVICES
CUTS, COLORS & STYLES

363
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:19,960
We're closed today.

364
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:23,280
I need a haircut.

365
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:37,960
<i>Xiaohe.</i>

366
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:39,960
Say hi to Uncle Ran.

367
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,440
Hello, Xiaohe.

368
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,520
This is for you.

369
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:49,920
<i>Thank you, Uncle Ran.</i>

370
00:31:58,280 --> 00:31:59,960
Let go of me. I'm not going with you.

371
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:02,120
I even treated you as my best friend!

372
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:07,720
Xiaohe, I owe you an apology.

373
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:11,640
The way you acted in the traffickers' van
was brave and smart.

374
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:13,280
You surely are cut out for a detective.

375
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,640
From now on, you teach me music notation,

376
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:19,960
I teach you criminal investigation.

377
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:21,040
We'll learn from each other.

378
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:23,880
- Deal.
- Deal.

379
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:46,160
RAN 1972-2003

380
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:07,760
TOMB OF RAN FANGXU

381
00:33:07,840 --> 00:33:08,880
First bow.

382
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:14,360
Second bow.

383
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:25,840
Third bow.

384
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:42,520
Uncle Ran.

385
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,040
Hello. My surname is Ran.

386
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:29,280
- Ran as in rising upward.
- This is my apprentice.

387
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,480
I'm not.

388
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:32,280
He's not my mentor.

389
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,560
Let me say this again.

390
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:35,680
I am not your apprentice.

391
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,600
He Yuanhang!

392
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:41,000
I got him! He Yuanhang.

393
00:36:41,080 --> 00:36:42,840
He Yuanhang,
you're not fit to be a detective!

394
00:36:42,920 --> 00:36:43,880
MISSING PERSON

395
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:54,800
I'll follow your lead.
Let's do the plan you talked about.

396
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:57,360
This time, you're the one who begged me.

397
00:36:58,040 --> 00:36:59,120
Aren't we partners?

398
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:02,840
Look at you.
You work pretty well together.

399
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:17,520
He!

400
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:19,480
He!

401
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:22,120
He!

402
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:24,400
Don't sleep, He.

403
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:26,120
Comrade He Yuanhang, you're hereby awarded

404
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:27,640
Second-class Merit for Individual Service.

405
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:41,960
I'm leaving,

406
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:43,880
sir.

407
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:54,520
Kiddo.

408
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:57,600
I only ask one thing of you.

409
00:37:58,600 --> 00:37:59,600
Dad,

410
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,240
say no more.

411
00:38:02,160 --> 00:38:05,200
After the holiday,
I'll go back to school and study.

412
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:06,720
I'll apply to the police academy

413
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:08,840
and become a detective.

414
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:10,520
I'll solve cases

415
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:13,000
and finish the shifts

416
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:16,040
for you all that you never got to finish.

417
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:27,800
TOMB OF RAN FANGXU

418
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:29,040
Uncle Ran,

419
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:31,360
I'm not going to Beijing anymore.

420
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:35,880
No matter how cold or heavy something is,

421
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:38,160
I'll carry it myself.

422
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:40,200
I'll carry it all by myself.

423
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:21,520
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH

424
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:26,160
<i>Wang Xinglong said</i>
<i>the night before New Year's Eve,</i>

425
00:39:26,240 --> 00:39:28,560
<i>Ran stayed in New York Block</i>
<i>the whole night.</i>

426
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:32,240
<i>He must've found</i>
<i>some crucial information or a clue.</i>

427
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,320
That's why the next day
he wrote that message.

428
00:39:36,200 --> 00:39:38,520
I'm not leaving this building.

429
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:41,720
I'll ask Captain Zhao
to reopen the June 30th case.

430
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:45,040
We'll reopen it, but now isn't the time.

431
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:46,400
<i>We don't have key evidence.</i>

432
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:49,600
<i>Especially this crucial person,</i>
<i>Yao Xincheng.</i>

433
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:50,920
We haven't found him yet.

434
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:52,560
Luckily,

435
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:55,720
Ran narrowed the final clue
down to Yuanlongli.

436
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:58,120
- I'll investigate with you.
- <i>No need.</i>

437
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,160
If we go together, we'll draw attention.

438
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:02,720
<i>It'll be easier if I work alone.</i>

439
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,160
<i>Get the application papers ready now.</i>

440
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:05,960
<i>Once I make progress here,</i>

441
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:09,640
go to Zhao Jie and have him coordinate
a delay to Yuanlongli's demolition.

442
00:40:10,560 --> 00:40:11,440
Also…

443
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:14,960
Hello? Hello?

444
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:16,080
Hello?

445
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:18,960
Lousy signal.

446
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,360
NO SERVICE

447
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:24,200
Jeez.

448
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:26,320
No signal again.

449
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,800
Mr. He,

450
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,200
you went back on your word.

451
00:40:45,280 --> 00:40:47,000
You said you would move out
before demolition.

452
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:48,200
You let down my trust.

453
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:50,320
Good timing.

454
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:53,920
Didn't you want me to move out early?
Find a person for me.

455
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:57,600
Ask around whether anyone
named Yao Xincheng

456
00:40:57,680 --> 00:41:00,560
was living in Yuanlongli around 1997.

457
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:03,120
Or anyone who knows this person.

458
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,080
- Yao Xincheng?
- Right.

459
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:09,200
Never heard of any Yao Xincheng.

460
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,000
Mr. He, tell me honestly.

461
00:41:12,080 --> 00:41:13,360
You refuse to leave here

462
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:15,640
because you want to investigate
the case from 1997 again?

463
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:18,480
Are you acting up again?

464
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:20,680
My mind is perfectly fine.

465
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:22,400
Don't listen to their nonsense.

466
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,720
Seems like you're still not quite right.

467
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:31,200
Mr. He, Officer Ran and you
solved the Yuanlongli case twice.

468
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,200
You even got a commendation
the second time.

469
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:36,160
Are you trying to overturn it
and solve it a third time?

470
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:39,400
Until the truth is found,
forget a third time.

471
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:40,840
A fourth time. A fifth time.

472
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:43,080
Even if it takes a hundred times,
I'll keep digging.

473
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:46,720
This is the task
Ran left me before he died.

474
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:48,160
If I can't finish it,

475
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:50,640
I won't have the face
to meet him down there.

476
00:41:54,240 --> 00:41:57,320
This was Officer Ran's last wish?

477
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:58,520
Right.

478
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:07,360
For someone as good as Officer Ran,

479
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:10,440
I'll help with this.

480
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:15,320
Tell me. Aside from Yao Xincheng,
what else do you need me to do?

481
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:20,680
Can you restore
the signal, water, and electricity?

482
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:22,520
- Alright.
- By the way,

483
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:26,880
if possible, tell Qian Dajun
not to start demolition early.

484
00:42:27,640 --> 00:42:28,720
I'll do everything I can to help.

485
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:32,120
Qian Dajun is downstairs.
Wait for my news.

486
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:34,040
Okay?

487
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:52,720
ROUND 4 OF THE TRÉMAUX ALGORITHM
ON THE YUANLONGLI CASE

488
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:09,960
HOLDOUTS GROUP

489
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:11,640
DU: MR. HE, HURRY OVER!

490
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,280
DU

491
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:16,600
<i>Mr. He, help me! Get to the cybercafé now!</i>

492
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:22,720
This man…

493
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,360
OPTICAL

494
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:25,640
Brat,

495
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:28,080
listen up.

496
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,000
Move aside right now.

497
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:32,400
My patience is running out.

498
00:43:33,160 --> 00:43:36,040
Don't come over! Don't come over!

499
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:37,400
I'll count to three.

500
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:40,080
If you don't move,

501
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:41,520
I'll tear down this darned building
with you in it.

502
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:43,000
I'll stand with my shop.

503
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:45,560
If you dare come closer,
I'll take you down with me!

504
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,040
One.

505
00:43:48,680 --> 00:43:49,960
Two.

506
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:52,600
- Three.
- Qian Dajun,

507
00:43:53,440 --> 00:43:55,280
what you're doing now counts as a crime.

508
00:43:55,360 --> 00:43:56,520
Get down here.

509
00:43:57,640 --> 00:43:58,800
Crazy old fool.

510
00:43:59,320 --> 00:44:01,000
Still think you're a cop?

511
00:44:03,360 --> 00:44:04,880
HAIR SALON

512
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:10,480
I'm fighting you today!

513
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:12,240
Come on then. Don't stop me, Mr. He!

514
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:13,520
I'll hack him to death!

515
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:16,680
Don't stop me, Mr. He!

516
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:17,640
I'll kill him!

517
00:44:17,720 --> 00:44:20,400
Don't stop me, Mr. He! I'll kill him!

518
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:24,000
I'll kill you!

519
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:25,200
Qian Dajun,

520
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:26,760
- I'll kill you!
- Darn it.

521
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:29,880
- My fence!
